obfuscateEmail()

Description
    obfuscateEmail(array $attrPairs)
	Obfuscates an e-mail message passed to the function.

Parameters
    attrPairs
		An array, $attPairs, containing the element $attPairs['email']
		
Return Values
    Returns a string value to the calling statement.

Notes
	Obfuscates the e-mail text by pre-pending '&#' to each character in the string and appending each with ';'.
	So the string "test email" becomes &#116;&#101;&#115;&#116;&#101;&#109;&#97;&#105;&#108;